{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_5253510b9b8745389773d6a2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Introduction\n2\t\n3\tWe welcome any and all contributions to Kedro, at whatever level you can manage. Here are some suggestions, but you are welcome to suggest anything else that you think improves the community for us all!\n4\t\n5\t## Join the community\n6\t\n7\tYou can find the Kedro community on our [Slack organisation](https://slack.kedro.org/), which is where we share news and announcements, and answer technical questions. You're welcome to post links to any articles or videos about Kedro that you create or find, such as how-tos, showcases, demos, blog posts or tutorials.\n8\t\n9\tWe also curate a [GitHub repo that lists content created by the Kedro community](https://github.com/kedro-org/awesome-kedro). If you've made something with Kedro, add it to the list with a PR!\n10\t\n11\t## Contribute to the project\n12\t\n13\tThere are several ways to contribute to Kedro, such as answering questions about Kedro to help others, fixing a typo on the documentation, reporting a bug, reviewing pull requests or adding a feature.\n14\t\n15\tTake a look at some of our [contribution suggestions on the Kedro GitHub Wiki](https://github.com/kedro-org/kedro/wiki/Contribute-to-Kedro)!\n16\t\n17\t## Join the Technical Steering Committee\n18\tKedro is an incubating project in [LF AI & Data](https://lfaidata.foundation/), a sub-organisation within the Linux Foundation that focuses on open innovation within the data and AI space.\n19\t\n20\tThe project is governed by a group of maintainers, known as the Technical Steering Committee (TSC); read more about the structure of our TSC in our [Technical Charter](./kedro_technical_charter.pdf).\n21\t\n22\tWe invite community members to join the TSC and help define the future of the Kedro project. Read the [guidance on becoming a Kedro maintainer](https://docs.kedro.org/en/stable/contribution/technical_steering_committee.html) to understand the process of joining the TSC.\n23\t\n24\t## Code of conduct\n25\t\n26\tThe Kedro team pledges to foster and maintain a friendly community. We enforce a [Code of Conduct](./CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) to ensure every Kedroid is welcomed and treated with respect.\n27\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09f1050b-b412-44b8-b8c6-34dc67aa5694","uuid":"56f8fdb6-f756-4bf1-998a-5ffdcd97e0bd","timestamp":"2026-04-06T09:16:48.607Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/CONTRIBUTING.md","content":"# Introduction\n\nWe welcome any and all contributions to Kedro, at whatever level you can manage. Here are some suggestions, but you are welcome to suggest anything else that you think improves the community for us all!\n\n## Join the community\n\nYou can find the Kedro community on our [Slack organisation](https://slack.kedro.org/), which is where we share news and announcements, and answer technical questions. You're welcome to post links to any articles or videos about Kedro that you create or find, such as how-tos, showcases, demos, blog posts or tutorials.\n\nWe also curate a [GitHub repo that lists content created by the Kedro community](https://github.com/kedro-org/awesome-kedro). If you've made something with Kedro, add it to the list with a PR!\n\n## Contribute to the project\n\nThere are several ways to contribute to Kedro, such as answering questions about Kedro to help others, fixing a typo on the documentation, reporting a bug, reviewing pull requests or adding a feature.\n\nTake a look at some of our [contribution suggestions on the Kedro GitHub Wiki](https://github.com/kedro-org/kedro/wiki/Contribute-to-Kedro)!\n\n## Join the Technical Steering Committee\nKedro is an incubating project in [LF AI & Data](https://lfaidata.foundation/), a sub-organisation within the Linux Foundation that focuses on open innovation within the data and AI space.\n\nThe project is governed by a group of maintainers, known as the Technical Steering Committee (TSC); read more about the structure of our TSC in our [Technical Charter](./kedro_technical_charter.pdf).\n\nWe invite community members to join the TSC and help define the future of the Kedro project. Read the [guidance on becoming a Kedro maintainer](https://docs.kedro.org/en/stable/contribution/technical_steering_committee.html) to understand the process of joining the TSC.\n\n## Code of conduct\n\nThe Kedro team pledges to foster and maintain a friendly community. We enforce a [Code of Conduct](./CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) to ensure every Kedroid is welcomed and treated with respect.\n","numLines":27,"startLine":1,"totalLines":27}}}
